Desi - yes, we have talked. When you were putting together new Wraith, you sent me a &quot;/who all cleric 60&quot; recruitment tell as Biffins. When I asked why Biffins wasn't in Vis Maior, you told me that he was a friend that had given you the account when he went to college. Later, I found out you'd bought Biffins from Eric. Which story is the truth?<br>
<br>
Talk to some ex-Wraith about you? You might not want to hear this, but some of the people most critical of you in our guild are ex-Wraith. I'm not going to get a very good picture of you talking to them.<br>
<br>
So I judge you by the actions of your guild when you're online, since you seem to be the senior officer in charge of a lot of things. Look at the list of things LC members have brought up here - not very impressive, is it? I judge you by the comments you make on your boards. Even a neutral third party like Gaethan finds them boastful. And the comment you made about &quot;no artificial limits on content&quot; was very provocative - does that mean you won't enter rotations if you think you can dominate a spawn, as many have interpreted it to mean?<br>
<br>
Just as PoP was coming out, I was poised to leave EQ and cancel my account. I did not think the core problems with the game could be resolved, and I'd rather do something constructive with my time. Then a close personal friend who was also going to quit told me he wasn't, so I was hovering on the edge of staying or going. That night, in The Bazaar, I overheard this:<br>
<br>
Behemoth pokes Dachunker.<br>
Behemoth says, &quot;HEY BLUE CON&quot;<br>
Behemoth pokes Dachunker.<br>
Behemoth says, &quot;HEY BLUE CON&quot;<br>
<br>
Repeat a few more times.<br>
<br>
That's when I decided I was staying to make sure that morons like Toobay could never, EVER achieve &quot;server best&quot;. I am entirely motivated by the desire to keep Wraith second or third best on Quellious, because of the arrogance and stupidity I see come from that guild day in and day out. I feel that this all stems from the leadership group, as they are the ones that decide guild policy (and most of the complaints you saw above were about guild actions, not individual actions). So that is why my ire is directed at you, Desi.<br>
<br>
